The paper discusses the use of topic modeling (LDA) on a text corpus, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) research (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of principal component analysis (PCA), which is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis (cs.IR, cs.LG). The paper's focus on the statistical properties of the document sets and the need for follow-up using domain-specific semantic maps suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL).
